#: ../../source/managing_account/07_managing_identities/managing_identities.rst:2
msgid "Managing identities"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_account/07_managing_identities/managing_identities.rst:4
msgid "Prerequisite"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_account/07_managing_identities/managing_identities.rst:7
msgid ""
"The Identities tab is only available if SAML is activated on the portal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_account/07_managing_identities/managing_identities.rst:9
msgid ""
"From the Identities tab, authenticated users have the possibility to manage "
"their SAML identities or to link their OpenDataSoft account to a SAML "
"identity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_account/07_managing_identities/managing_identities.rst:11
msgid ""
"The content of the Identities tab depends on the type of the user. There are"
" 3 types of users in OpenDataSoft: OpenDataSoft users, local users and "
"linked users (more information in :doc:`the SAML documentation "
"</configuring_domain/01_managing_security/saml>`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_account/07_managing_identities/managing_identities.rst:14
msgid "Identities tab for OpenDataSoft users"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_account/07_managing_identities/managing_identities.rst:18
msgid ""
"For OpenDataSoft users, the Identities tab only contains a link that allows "
"OpenDataSoft users to link their OpenDataSoft account to a SAML identity. It"
" makes them become linked users, which changes the content of the Identity "
"tab."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_account/07_managing_identities/managing_identities.rst:20
msgid ""
"To link the account to a SAML account, click the \"Link your account to a "
"SAML account on this domain\" link."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_account/07_managing_identities/managing_identities.rst:23
msgid "Identities tab for local and linked users"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_account/07_managing_identities/managing_identities.rst:27
msgid ""
"For both local and linked users, the Identities tab contains information "
"about the SAML identity. Each SAML identity is represented by a rectangle "
"which contains all identity attributes sent by the identity provider."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_account/07_managing_identities/managing_identities.rst:29
msgid ""
"For linked users only, a \"Revoke\" button is also displayed at the top "
"right corner of the SAML identity rectangle. It allows to revoke the SAML "
"identity without deleting the OpenDataSoft account: it makes the linked "
"users become OpenDataSoft users."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_account/07_managing_identities/managing_identities.rst:31
msgid "To revoke a SAML identity:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_account/07_managing_identities/managing_identities.rst:33
msgid "Click on the Revoke button. A confirmation pop up window appears."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_account/07_managing_identities/managing_identities.rst:34
msgid "Click on the OK button to confirm."
msgstr ""
